1
00:00:45,519 --> 00:00:48,352
(thunder booming)

2
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:57,617
(airplane buzzing)

3
00:01:00,767 --> 00:01:03,684
(thunder cracking)

4
00:01:30,891 --> 00:01:33,113
- [Phantom Narrating] My
name is Phantom F. Harlock.

5
00:01:35,940 --> 00:01:39,840
It was when I was flying in a thunderstorm

6
00:01:39,840 --> 00:01:41,780
from Port Moresby across New Guinea

7
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:46,463
heading for Rabaul in New Britain.

8
00:01:49,180 --> 00:01:53,660
As an ariel explorer my
life long cherished dream

9
00:01:53,660 --> 00:01:56,333
was to conquer the air
throughout the whole world.

10
00:01:59,090 --> 00:02:00,840
The only thing that stood in my way

11
00:02:01,930 --> 00:02:04,293
were the Owen Stanley Mountains.

12
00:02:06,230 --> 00:02:07,830
With its highest peak soaring up

13
00:02:07,830 --> 00:02:10,200
to 5,030 meters above sea level

14
00:02:11,380 --> 00:02:13,300
the mountain people feared

15
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:17,253
calling it the Witch of
the Owen Stanley range.

16
00:02:18,220 --> 00:02:22,390
My name is Phantom F.
Harlock and this plane

17
00:02:22,390 --> 00:02:25,473
I call Arcadia is like
my own flesh and blood.

18
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:31,600
My companion to share my
fate and my youth in Arcadia.

19
00:02:34,190 --> 00:02:37,620
Sharing those precious youthful days.

20
00:02:37,620 --> 00:02:39,333
Flying high in the sky.

21
00:02:41,179 --> 00:02:45,230
If it ever ceases to fly my
life will come to and end.

22
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:50,910
With a full load of fuel the
plane was heavy that day.

23
00:02:52,450 --> 00:02:53,810
I couldn't gain any altitude

24
00:02:53,810 --> 00:02:56,513
and Arcadian's engine gasped desperately.

25
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,540
The sound from the gasping cylinders

26
00:03:00,910 --> 00:03:04,593
was almost like my aged
irregular heartbeat.

27
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,983
I and my Arcadia flew through
ravines wherever possible.

28
00:03:13,545 --> 00:03:18,545
(airplane buzzing)
(dramatic music)

29
00:03:35,490 --> 00:03:39,700
But the Owen Stanley
Mountains just stood there

30
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:44,700
high and rigid and cold, totally
dominating Arcadia and me.

31
00:03:49,824 --> 00:03:52,324
(tense music)

32
00:04:37,190 --> 00:04:40,610
Arcadia and me, we had
to face bitter defeat

33
00:04:40,610 --> 00:04:43,673
for the first time in our
entire life in the sky.

34
00:04:44,770 --> 00:04:47,400
While turning back swallowing my pride

35
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:49,766
something made me look back.

36
00:04:49,766 --> 00:04:52,683
(echoing laughing)

37
00:04:56,972 --> 00:05:00,063
The mountain, the mountain was laughing.

38
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:03,940
With my Arcadia I had
been continuously blind

39
00:05:03,940 --> 00:05:05,790
believing we could never be defeated.

40
00:05:09,030 --> 00:05:11,400
I jettisoned all the fuel only

41
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:14,010
leaving enough for 10 minutes of flight.

42
00:05:14,010 --> 00:05:16,450
Lightening the plane I'd staked

43
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:18,463
everything on those last 10 minutes.

44
00:05:22,157 --> 00:05:24,907
(dramatic music)

45
00:05:32,060 --> 00:05:34,560
My name is Phantom F. Harlock.

46
00:05:35,980 --> 00:05:39,150
The plane and I shared
every moment of my life.

47
00:05:39,150 --> 00:05:42,470
My youth and Arcadia, the life I lived

48
00:05:42,470 --> 00:05:44,363
flying in the sky with conviction.

49
00:05:45,380 --> 00:05:49,760
There is no regret so
long as men do not abandon

50
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:53,417
their dreams their
dreams will never vanish.

51
00:06:01,318 --> 00:06:06,318
(echoing laughing)
(dramatic music)

52
00:06:17,388 --> 00:06:20,305
(thunder cracking)

53
00:06:21,709 --> 00:06:26,709
(echoing laughing)
(dramatic music)

54
00:06:45,860 --> 00:06:50,860
(thunder cracking)
(echoing laughing)

55
00:07:10,308 --> 00:07:13,225
(orchestral music)

56
00:08:00,089 --> 00:08:03,344
(glass shattering)

57
00:08:03,344 --> 00:08:05,677
(screaming)

58
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:12,027
(glass shattering)
(gasping)

59
00:08:12,027 --> 00:08:15,110
- [Man] The third clock,
impact gun damaged.

60
00:08:15,110 --> 00:08:17,070
- [Man] Starboard rear
engine room damaged.

61
00:08:17,070 --> 00:08:19,390
- [Man] The ship's thrust 80%.

62
00:08:19,390 --> 00:08:21,060
- [Man] An enemy's ship approaching.

63
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:23,313
Take phase three combat position.

64
00:08:24,745 --> 00:08:27,495
(dramatic music)

65
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:24,540
- [Phantom] The dream is over now.

66
00:09:24,540 --> 00:09:26,940
Earth is the only place
where Earthmen can live.

67
00:09:32,150 --> 00:09:35,333
We must submit to defeat,
but have we done our best?

68
00:09:36,292 --> 00:09:37,125
Hmm.

69
00:09:37,970 --> 00:09:41,690
- [Man] This is Illumidus
Earth Occupation Force calling.

70
00:09:41,690 --> 00:09:44,783
Follow our instructions and
land your ship at base 446.

71
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:48,390
If you resist we will take immediate

72
00:09:48,390 --> 00:09:50,530
measures to destroy your ship.

73
00:09:50,530 --> 00:09:54,330
Six minutes, 55 seconds before touchdown.

74
00:09:54,330 --> 00:09:57,360
Maintain present course
and strike your colors.

75
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:59,357
Do not attempt to resist.

76
00:10:28,130 --> 00:10:31,133
- [Maya On Radio] Broadcasting
on frequency band 6050.

77
00:10:33,310 --> 00:10:36,500
With variable micro-frequency.

78
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:39,810
The sun disappeared yesterday,

79
00:10:39,810 --> 00:10:42,720
but the sun will rise again today.

80
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:45,707
Continue to have faith
in the ever rising sun.

81
00:10:47,549 --> 00:10:50,950
- That, that voice is--
- Believe in our future.

82
00:10:50,950 --> 00:10:52,583
Everyone living on Earth.

83
00:10:56,180 --> 00:10:59,735
Although the ground has been burnt--

84
00:10:59,735 --> 00:11:00,568
- [Phantom] Maya.

85
00:11:00,568 --> 00:11:02,440
- [Maya On Radio] Turning
everything into ashes.

86
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:04,700
All will revive again.

87
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:06,890
The sky is ever so blue.

88
00:11:07,970 --> 00:11:11,040
The sound of the ocean unchanged.

89
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:14,147
This is our own planet, Earth,

90
00:11:15,620 --> 00:11:18,753
so long as we keep our dreams.

91
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:25,123
- Oh, listen, that's the
underground radio from Earth.

92
00:11:26,230 --> 00:11:27,152
- [Maya On Radio] It will never disappear.

93
00:11:27,152 --> 00:11:29,600
- That's right, it's the
voice of Radio Free Arcadia

94
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:32,400
broadcasting from somewhere
on occupied Earth.

95
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:36,122
- [Maya On Radio] Keep a song
in your heart for tomorrow.

96
00:11:36,122 --> 00:11:40,580
Let us stop crying and
stand firmly on the ground

97
00:11:40,580 --> 00:11:43,327
for we shall all have a wonderful future.

98
00:11:44,675 --> 00:11:47,425
(dramatic music)

99
00:13:24,079 --> 00:13:26,329
(clanging)

100
00:13:36,176 --> 00:13:38,509
(screaming)

101
00:13:51,918 --> 00:13:54,168
(whirring)

102
00:14:10,490 --> 00:14:13,189
- Stupid landing.
- That stumblebum.

103
00:14:13,189 --> 00:14:14,480
No wonder we lost the battle.

104
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:16,120
- [Man] The Solar Federation.
(mocking laughing)

105
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,603
Some invincible armada.

106
00:14:18,543 --> 00:14:20,314
- Move, move.
(gasping)

107
00:14:20,314 --> 00:14:21,147
- Move.

108
00:14:25,495 --> 00:14:27,846
(footsteps rapidly thudding)

109
00:14:27,846 --> 00:14:30,846
(suspenseful music)

110
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:36,193
- Captain, isn't your name Harlock?

111
00:14:38,300 --> 00:14:39,750
Remember you're surrendering.

112
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,603
I'll take your sidearm.

113
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:52,310
A very amateurish landing,

114
00:14:52,310 --> 00:14:53,520
but I guess it was inevitable

115
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:56,290
due to the poor condition of the runway.

116
00:14:56,290 --> 00:15:00,320
Still, I think your secret
purpose was to disable your ship.

117
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:01,153
- That's right.

118
00:15:03,050 --> 00:15:05,110
- [Zoll] You are to present
yourself to headquarters

119
00:15:05,110 --> 00:15:07,210
and that will conclude all of your duties.

120
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:11,083
- Haven't we met before?

121
00:15:13,030 --> 00:15:15,900
- During the battle at the
Castlemagne Star Cluster

122
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:18,963
you disabled my ship by
blowing a hole in the hull.

123
00:15:19,820 --> 00:15:20,900
- I see.

124
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:22,900
Now that you've won you must feel great.

125
00:15:23,750 --> 00:15:25,100
- It was a very long battle

126
00:15:25,950 --> 00:15:29,380
and many times I felt
my last hour had come.

127
00:15:29,380 --> 00:15:32,550
You were a formidable
adversary, especially your ship.

128
00:15:32,550 --> 00:15:33,383
- Thank you.

129
00:15:36,437 --> 00:15:38,180
And what is your name?

130
00:15:38,180 --> 00:15:39,603
- Zoll, of Tokarga.
- Torkarga.

131
00:15:41,770 --> 00:15:43,470
Planet Torkarga?

132
00:15:43,470 --> 00:15:45,870
That lost the war against
Illumidus a long time ago?

133
00:15:45,870 --> 00:15:46,703
- That's right.

134
00:15:48,196 --> 00:15:51,196
(suspenseful music)

135
00:15:57,202 --> 00:15:58,952
Report at 10 o'clock.

136
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:07,273
Wait.

137
00:16:09,830 --> 00:16:10,700
Didn't you hear me?

138
00:16:10,700 --> 00:16:12,853
I told you to report to headquarters.

139
00:16:13,930 --> 00:16:16,220
- [Phantom] I still have
two hours before 10 o'clock

140
00:16:16,220 --> 00:16:17,870
and there's a place I wish to go.

141
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:23,373
- Your families' place?

142
00:16:24,290 --> 00:16:25,743
- I have no family.

143
00:16:31,060 --> 00:16:33,490
- Remember to report at 10 o'clock.

144
00:16:33,490 --> 00:16:34,830
- I will be there.

145
00:16:34,830 --> 00:16:37,420
What's wrong, don't you trust my word?

146
00:16:37,420 --> 00:16:39,210
- Just be careful walking in the streets.

147
00:16:39,210 --> 00:16:42,453
If you get killed and fail to
return I'll be responsible.

148
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:55,993
- [Maya On Radio] This is
the voice of Free Arcadia.

149
00:16:56,910 --> 00:17:00,593
The sun set but it will rise again.

150
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:05,813
There's no future for those who
don't believe in the future.

151
00:17:06,970 --> 00:17:11,010
The ones who believe have endured.

152
00:17:11,010 --> 00:17:15,360
Some day we will meet again
and some day join forces

153
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:18,213
to start living our future together.

154
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:21,903
Don't let the fire die down.

155
00:17:22,810 --> 00:17:24,940
Keep even the faintest spark

156
00:17:26,210 --> 00:17:28,960
with a firm belief in our future.

157
00:17:31,736 --> 00:17:33,062
(footsteps rapidly thudding)

158
00:17:33,062 --> 00:17:35,562
(guns firing)

159
00:17:36,788 --> 00:17:38,676
(screaming)

160
00:17:38,676 --> 00:17:40,677
- [Man] Over here.

161
00:17:40,677 --> 00:17:43,427
(dramatic music)

162
00:17:52,854 --> 00:17:53,687
(thumping)
(groaning)

163
00:17:53,687 --> 00:17:57,605
(gun firing)
(thumping)

164
00:17:57,605 --> 00:17:59,772
(yelling)

165
00:18:02,104 --> 00:18:04,176
(gun firing)

166
00:18:04,176 --> 00:18:06,343
(yelling)

167
00:18:08,252 --> 00:18:11,003
(clanging)

168
00:18:11,003 --> 00:18:13,753
(dramatic music)

169
00:18:40,850 --> 00:18:43,010
- I see no reason not to use a man

170
00:18:43,010 --> 00:18:45,900
who won the highest hero medal in combat.

171
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:46,733
- Sir.

172
00:18:57,230 --> 00:19:00,193
- Apparently Zoll you thought
too highly of the Earth man.

173
00:19:11,055 --> 00:19:13,805
(dramatic music)

174
00:19:18,820 --> 00:19:19,653
- I am here.

175
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:23,283
What do you want of me?

176
00:19:24,420 --> 00:19:26,610
- This is the Illumidus Occupation Forces'

177
00:19:26,610 --> 00:19:28,333
supreme commander General Zeda.

178
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:30,883
- And I am Harlock.

179
00:19:33,290 --> 00:19:35,570
The captain of the Death Shadow.

180
00:19:35,570 --> 00:19:37,670
And there's nothing more to say.

181
00:19:37,670 --> 00:19:39,763
- Don't get smart Earth man.

182
00:19:47,152 --> 00:19:52,152
(bones cracking)
(groaning)

183
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:01,273
- Let go of him Harlock.

184
00:20:07,220 --> 00:20:10,330
Reading books is not going
to help you win any battles.

185
00:20:10,330 --> 00:20:13,093
Books will never help you win against us.

186
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:22,290
- We've gathered a
staggering amount of data

187
00:20:22,290 --> 00:20:25,282
on you Earthmen since our occupation

188
00:20:25,282 --> 00:20:27,610
and according to our computer analysis

189
00:20:27,610 --> 00:20:30,450
Earthmen are easily acclimated
to a new environment.

190
00:20:30,450 --> 00:20:33,350
In other words even though
they've been hostile

191
00:20:33,350 --> 00:20:36,820
up until today now they're
wagging their tails at us.

192
00:20:36,820 --> 00:20:39,883
- But the fact is Earthmen
are definitely not cowards.

193
00:20:40,990 --> 00:20:43,207
- [La Mime] Let me present
Prime Minister Triter

194
00:20:43,207 --> 00:20:45,043
of the Illumidus Occupation cabinet.

195
00:20:46,060 --> 00:20:49,280
- Ah, good evening.
- Prime Minister Triter

196
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:52,050
I see you have failed to
capture The Rose once again.

197
00:20:52,050 --> 00:20:54,860
- Ah well, I assure you that I will

198
00:20:54,860 --> 00:20:56,590
arrest and execute her the next time.

199
00:20:56,590 --> 00:20:58,660
- My orders are to identify the voice

200
00:20:58,660 --> 00:21:02,180
of Free Arcadia at any
cost, not to execute anyone.

201
00:21:02,180 --> 00:21:04,340
And once we find out there are ways

202
00:21:04,340 --> 00:21:05,640
of taking advantage of it.

203
00:21:07,986 --> 00:21:10,120
- Oh, this man is--

204
00:21:10,120 --> 00:21:12,720
- The ex-captain of the evacuation ship.

205
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:15,873
- Ah, Harlock, this man is dangerous.

206
00:21:17,406 --> 00:21:19,573
(gasping)

207
00:21:20,960 --> 00:21:23,693
Well, if you'll excuse
me, I have things to do.

208
00:21:27,710 --> 00:21:29,013
- A useless individual.

209
00:21:35,787 --> 00:21:38,090
- By the way Harlock General Zeda

210
00:21:38,090 --> 00:21:39,580
has seen your combat record

211
00:21:39,580 --> 00:21:40,880
and is willing to give you work,

212
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:42,850
that is if you want the job.

213
00:21:42,850 --> 00:21:44,040
- I decline.

214
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:46,563
- So you are also stubborn, you may leave.

215
00:21:49,890 --> 00:21:51,910
- Take your food coupons and get lost.

216
00:21:51,910 --> 00:21:54,150
Go anywhere, there is
nothing for you to do.

217
00:21:54,150 --> 00:21:57,150
You will never have another
chance to fly again, understand?

218
00:22:00,410 --> 00:22:02,293
La Mime, give him some coupons.

219
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:05,370
- [La Mime] Just a moment please.

220
00:22:09,610 --> 00:22:11,550
Your food coupons.

221
00:22:11,550 --> 00:22:14,493
Keep your temper and eat while you can.

222
00:22:17,320 --> 00:22:19,840
The provisions on Earth are running short.

223
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:21,853
Eat now or you'll starve to death.

224
00:22:29,711 --> 00:22:34,544
(jazz music)
(chattering)

225
00:22:56,250 --> 00:22:58,180
- Hey, this guy has a black collar.

226
00:22:58,180 --> 00:22:59,790
Why don't we show him some fun?

227
00:22:59,790 --> 00:23:02,010
- Leave him alone, he might be the one

228
00:23:02,010 --> 00:23:04,710
who scratched one of our ships in battle.

229
00:23:04,710 --> 00:23:05,920
- Scratched our ship?

230
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:08,793
I bet you're right.
(laughing)

231
00:23:20,909 --> 00:23:22,424
- Hmm?

232
00:23:22,424 --> 00:23:25,174
(dramatic music)

233
00:23:36,162 --> 00:23:39,579
- [Phantom Thinking] I know how you feel.

234
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:44,860
All we can do now is eat and wait.

235
00:23:44,860 --> 00:23:47,333
We've been defeated but we still exist.

236
00:24:08,180 --> 00:24:09,393
- Just don't die.

237
00:24:14,109 --> 00:24:15,700
(laughing)

238
00:24:15,700 --> 00:24:17,900
- [Phantom] And I was
feeling sorry for him.

239
00:24:24,586 --> 00:24:26,836
(groaning)

240
00:24:29,330 --> 00:24:31,493
- Why you dirty yellow rat.

241
00:24:32,430 --> 00:24:35,443
Take that and go back to
the gutter where you belong.

242
00:24:38,620 --> 00:24:41,130
And now you're stealing my food.

243
00:24:48,765 --> 00:24:50,364
(groaning)

244
00:24:50,364 --> 00:24:55,364
- That'll fix him.
(laughing)

245
00:24:56,324 --> 00:24:57,611
(groaning)

246
00:24:57,611 --> 00:24:58,444
- Well?

247
00:25:00,918 --> 00:25:03,168
(groaning)

248
00:25:04,379 --> 00:25:06,629
(laughing)

249
00:25:10,449 --> 00:25:12,699
(thumping)

250
00:25:13,556 --> 00:25:16,141
(chuckling)

251
00:25:16,141 --> 00:25:17,303
(grunting)

252
00:25:17,303 --> 00:25:19,553
(thumping)

253
00:25:38,249 --> 00:25:39,332
- Go get him!

254
00:25:40,169 --> 00:25:42,919
(angry shouting)

255
00:25:44,065 --> 00:25:46,315
(thudding)

256
00:25:49,070 --> 00:25:51,237
(bonking)

257
00:25:56,455 --> 00:25:58,705
(groaning)

258
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:02,850
(laughing)

259
00:26:14,141 --> 00:26:16,391
(thumping)

260
00:26:18,298 --> 00:26:21,044
- Now that things have gone
this far, drop dead all of you!

261
00:26:21,044 --> 00:26:23,294
(laughing)

262
00:26:27,123 --> 00:26:29,373
(thumping)

263
00:26:34,265 --> 00:26:35,098
Whoa.

264
00:26:36,147 --> 00:26:39,104
(thumping)

265
00:26:39,104 --> 00:26:41,354
(laughing)

266
00:26:44,510 --> 00:26:45,435
- [Woman] Huh?

267
00:26:45,435 --> 00:26:47,018
What are you doing?

268
00:26:48,628 --> 00:26:51,378
(sirens blaring)

269
00:26:53,630 --> 00:26:54,463
(laughing)

270
00:26:54,463 --> 00:26:55,470
- That was fun.

271
00:26:55,470 --> 00:26:57,940
My name is Tochiro and I'm leaving now.

272
00:26:57,940 --> 00:26:59,248
- So am I.

273
00:26:59,248 --> 00:27:01,998
(sirens blaring)

274
00:27:12,188 --> 00:27:13,552
(cat scowling)

275
00:27:13,552 --> 00:27:17,278
(glass shattering)

276
00:27:17,278 --> 00:27:18,528
- What a waste.

277
00:27:20,500 --> 00:27:24,403
- But why, why do you go
around acting like a beggar?

278
00:27:25,970 --> 00:27:28,350
- [Tochiro] You could call
it a single handed revolt.

279
00:27:28,350 --> 00:27:29,183
- Revolt?

280
00:27:31,570 --> 00:27:33,470
- [Tochiro] That's right.

281
00:27:33,470 --> 00:27:34,303
- [Phantom] How can you call it

282
00:27:34,303 --> 00:27:35,973
a revolt without any weapons?

283
00:27:38,560 --> 00:27:41,770
- [Tochiro] If you had a
weapon would you revolt?

284
00:27:41,770 --> 00:27:42,603
- Weapon?

285
00:27:43,560 --> 00:27:45,685
But they're impossible to get.

286
00:27:45,685 --> 00:27:47,000
(laughing)

287
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:49,650
- [Tochiro] But there's
always a way to get anything.

288
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:51,753
Here.

289
00:27:53,630 --> 00:27:56,880
- Why that's-- Sort of old though.

290
00:27:56,880 --> 00:28:00,343
But how did you?
- Better than nothing.

291
00:28:01,494 --> 00:28:04,577
(vehicle screeching)

292
00:28:06,730 --> 00:28:08,509
- Someone is coming.

293
00:28:08,509 --> 00:28:10,926
(gun firing)

294
00:28:20,060 --> 00:28:22,210
- [Zoll] Brought you here
because the memory areas

295
00:28:22,210 --> 00:28:23,460
of both of your genes were

296
00:28:23,460 --> 00:28:25,740
put through analysis simultaneously

297
00:28:26,700 --> 00:28:29,910
and we analyzed 3,000 years of your past.

298
00:28:29,910 --> 00:28:31,180
- Why'd you do that?

299
00:28:31,180 --> 00:28:33,040
- Is this a torture? (yelling)

300
00:28:33,040 --> 00:28:34,550
- [Zoll] Listen to me.

301
00:28:34,550 --> 00:28:36,963
You both have the same common gene factor.

302
00:28:37,900 --> 00:28:40,250
See where those two lines
overlap now and then,

303
00:28:41,310 --> 00:28:42,710
the place where it sparkles.

304
00:28:43,780 --> 00:28:45,820
- [Phantom] What does that mean?

305
00:28:45,820 --> 00:28:47,710
- [Zoll] It indicates your memories.

306
00:28:47,710 --> 00:28:50,400
Both of you have inherited
some identical memory genes

307
00:28:50,400 --> 00:28:52,543
going back to your distant ancestors.

308
00:28:53,537 --> 00:28:55,010
- Identical?

309
00:28:55,010 --> 00:28:56,170
- With me?

310
00:28:56,170 --> 00:28:57,840
- Some time ago I happened to obtain

311
00:28:57,840 --> 00:29:00,113
some strange data on both of your genes.

312
00:29:00,960 --> 00:29:02,090
Both of you show the same

313
00:29:02,090 --> 00:29:05,170
memory based on a common experience.

314
00:29:05,170 --> 00:29:08,313
Now I am going to revive
that memory for you to see.

315
00:29:09,665 --> 00:29:12,582
(machine whirring)

316
00:29:32,638 --> 00:29:35,388
(dramatic music)

317
00:29:38,709 --> 00:29:41,126
(gun firing)

318
00:29:54,133 --> 00:29:54,970
- Follow me.

319
00:29:54,970 --> 00:29:57,643
We'll land on the autobahn for refueling.

320
00:30:00,989 --> 00:30:03,989
(airplanes buzzing)

321
00:30:14,488 --> 00:30:16,821
(screaming)

322
00:30:21,046 --> 00:30:23,296
(clanging)

323
00:30:28,012 --> 00:30:31,012
Well I guess that does it this time.

324
00:30:32,210 --> 00:30:34,840
- [Tochiro] Why are you waiting there?

325
00:30:34,840 --> 00:30:36,640
Get out of there before it blows up.

326
00:30:37,671 --> 00:30:39,460
- This, I've got to...

327
00:30:41,008 --> 00:30:42,860
- Ah, a C-12-D.

328
00:30:42,860 --> 00:30:45,010
- [Phantom] This gun
sight has never failed me.

329
00:30:45,010 --> 00:30:46,963
In the Battle of Britain or in Africa.

330
00:30:49,310 --> 00:30:50,260
What are you doing?

331
00:30:52,418 --> 00:30:55,335
(flames whooshing)

332
00:31:03,880 --> 00:31:06,880
(explosion booming)

333
00:31:08,075 --> 00:31:10,825
(dramatic music)

334
00:31:17,170 --> 00:31:19,720
- It's too bad your plane
was destroyed like that.

335
00:31:19,720 --> 00:31:22,313
- Ah, I never thought that would happen.

336
00:31:23,550 --> 00:31:26,150
- Your landing gear wasn't strong enough.

337
00:31:26,150 --> 00:31:27,433
It's not your fault.

338
00:31:28,880 --> 00:31:30,500
- Are you Japanese?

339
00:31:30,500 --> 00:31:31,350
- Yes.

340
00:31:31,350 --> 00:31:32,840
I came on a technical exchange

341
00:31:32,840 --> 00:31:34,260
as an optical instrument designer.

342
00:31:34,260 --> 00:31:35,930
My name is Tochiro Oyama.

343
00:31:35,930 --> 00:31:38,990
- I'm Phantom F. Harlock Junior.

344
00:31:38,990 --> 00:31:42,910
- Harlock, then you're the
one who wrote this book huh?

345
00:31:42,910 --> 00:31:44,870
- My father wrote it.

346
00:31:44,870 --> 00:31:48,130
- I see, My Youth in Arcadia.

347
00:31:48,130 --> 00:31:50,720
Only real men could understand this book.

348
00:31:50,720 --> 00:31:51,553
- Maybe.

349
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:55,570
- [Tochiro] But why are you
flying an Iron Cross plane?

350
00:31:55,570 --> 00:31:57,420
- I'm just doing it to pay the rent.

351
00:31:57,420 --> 00:32:02,060
By the way Tochiro are you a samurai?

352
00:32:02,060 --> 00:32:03,710
- [Tochiro] My father's a farmer.

353
00:32:08,480 --> 00:32:10,330
The first manned rocket in the world.

354
00:32:13,377 --> 00:32:16,210
(explosion booming)

355
00:32:16,210 --> 00:32:18,630
- I guess it ran out of fuel.

356
00:32:18,630 --> 00:32:21,320
- A lot of things are
running out fuel these days.

357
00:32:21,320 --> 00:32:23,383
- But my battle's not finished yet.

358
00:32:24,380 --> 00:32:27,180
- [Man] We've put all the
remaining fuel in that new one.

359
00:32:27,180 --> 00:32:28,433
It's the only plane left.

360
00:32:30,233 --> 00:32:32,983
(dramatic music)

361
00:32:44,313 --> 00:32:46,480
(gasping)

362
00:32:50,950 --> 00:32:52,210
- Why did you do that?

363
00:32:52,210 --> 00:32:55,420
No wonder this country isn't
going to last much longer.

364
00:32:55,420 --> 00:32:57,743
- [Phantom] Are you interested
in things like that?

365
00:32:58,670 --> 00:32:59,503
- That's right.

366
00:32:59,503 --> 00:33:02,270
My work is to develop
a new precision sight.

367
00:33:02,270 --> 00:33:04,240
I was handling it very carefully,

368
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:07,320
but your rough landing on the
road caused it to be smashed.

369
00:33:07,320 --> 00:33:10,370
- I'm sorry.
- This is a stupid war.

370
00:33:10,370 --> 00:33:12,573
- I guess we're both feeling frustrated.

371
00:33:14,090 --> 00:33:16,490
- If they'd only let me work
without all this fighting

372
00:33:16,490 --> 00:33:17,900
I could work on a great project

373
00:33:17,900 --> 00:33:20,880
with a future in it
like going to the moon.

374
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:22,460
- There'll come a time some day

375
00:33:23,300 --> 00:33:25,123
when man will be able to go there.

376
00:33:33,892 --> 00:33:38,892
(airplanes buzzing)
(guns firing)

377
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:06,810
Tochiro what's wrong?

378
00:34:06,810 --> 00:34:07,790
Hurry and go.

379
00:34:07,790 --> 00:34:10,330
- But there's no place where I can go.

380
00:34:10,330 --> 00:34:13,740
- Go to Wiesbaden and then to Switzerland.

381
00:34:13,740 --> 00:34:16,370
- The Allies already
took Wiesbaden last week

382
00:34:16,370 --> 00:34:19,170
and they're between here and
the Swiss border right now.

383
00:34:20,680 --> 00:34:23,978
But I sure wish I could continue
my research in Switzerland.

384
00:34:23,978 --> 00:34:25,858
(bomb whistling)

385
00:34:25,858 --> 00:34:28,858
(explosion booming)

386
00:34:36,085 --> 00:34:37,690
- [Phantom] There's not
much room, but get in there.

387
00:34:37,690 --> 00:34:40,680
It's not bulletproof so if
you get hit don't blame me.

388
00:34:40,680 --> 00:34:42,730
- [Tochiro] Don't worry, I'll be alright.

389
00:34:44,700 --> 00:34:47,700
(suspenseful music)

390
00:34:49,181 --> 00:34:51,348
(gasping)

391
00:34:52,191 --> 00:34:55,191
(suspenseful music)

392
00:35:06,587 --> 00:35:08,754
- Hang on, here they come.

393
00:35:10,751 --> 00:35:13,251
(guns firing)

394
00:35:39,552 --> 00:35:41,127
Tochiro, you alright?

395
00:35:41,127 --> 00:35:44,241
- [Tochiro] I've got a good view.

396
00:35:44,241 --> 00:35:45,987
Here comes a Spitfire on the right.

397
00:35:45,987 --> 00:35:47,283
- And here we go.

398
00:35:59,156 --> 00:36:00,547
And now.

399
00:36:00,547 --> 00:36:02,964
(gun firing)

400
00:36:08,616 --> 00:36:10,237
Strange, no rudder.

401
00:36:11,338 --> 00:36:13,833
Tochiro are there any
broken wires back there?

402
00:36:14,970 --> 00:36:17,033
- Everything is fine.
- Is it?

403
00:36:18,823 --> 00:36:20,063
A strange reaction.

404
00:36:22,130 --> 00:36:23,123
Got to get lower.

405
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:30,003
So, I'm the only one left.

406
00:36:32,202 --> 00:36:34,952
(dramatic music)

407
00:36:51,410 --> 00:36:52,243
Switzerland.

408
00:36:55,400 --> 00:36:56,753
10 more minutes.

409
00:37:07,240 --> 00:37:10,660
Tochiro, you want to go back to Japan?

410
00:37:10,660 --> 00:37:12,091
- [Tochiro] Of course I do.

411
00:37:12,091 --> 00:37:14,010
Harlock, don't you want to go home?

412
00:37:14,010 --> 00:37:14,843
- I do.

413
00:37:21,530 --> 00:37:23,453
And I want to return to Arcadia,

414
00:37:24,710 --> 00:37:27,340
the home of forests and lakes

415
00:37:27,340 --> 00:37:30,120
and a beautiful paradise like
the one in ancient Greece

416
00:37:31,710 --> 00:37:33,450
where my memories of youth go racing

417
00:37:33,450 --> 00:37:35,203
through the rich green fields.

418
00:37:36,330 --> 00:37:38,773
The home of the pirate
knight Harlock family.

419
00:37:40,240 --> 00:37:42,600
As the end of the journey approaches

420
00:37:42,600 --> 00:37:45,603
all my clansmen yearn to
return to our lovely home.

421
00:37:46,580 --> 00:37:48,700
We all hear the voice of the spirit

422
00:37:48,700 --> 00:37:50,320
of the pirate knight of Arcadia.

423
00:37:55,650 --> 00:37:59,282
(engine rumbling)

424
00:37:59,282 --> 00:38:01,865
(wind howling)

425
00:38:10,007 --> 00:38:12,590
Tochiro, next stop Switzerland.

426
00:38:17,078 --> 00:38:21,497
500 meters.

427
00:38:31,477 --> 00:38:34,430
Tochiro Switzerland is just on
the other side of that river.

428
00:38:34,430 --> 00:38:35,263
Hurry up.

429
00:38:36,220 --> 00:38:37,120
Come on out.

430
00:38:37,120 --> 00:38:37,953
What's wrong?

431
00:38:45,211 --> 00:38:46,841
(suspenseful music)

432
00:38:46,841 --> 00:38:49,091
(groaning)

433
00:38:53,930 --> 00:38:55,743
Tochiro, your hands.

434
00:38:57,460 --> 00:39:00,753
You held the broken wire
together with your bare hands.

435
00:39:01,750 --> 00:39:03,683
That's why the pedals felt so strange.

436
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:07,730
I'm sorry Tochiro, I didn't know.

437
00:39:07,730 --> 00:39:09,350
- But I'm not dead.

438
00:39:09,350 --> 00:39:11,450
It's just my hands, they're a little numb.

439
00:39:19,070 --> 00:39:20,070
- Wait for a second.

440
00:39:21,189 --> 00:39:22,022
- [Man] Hey over here.

441
00:39:22,022 --> 00:39:24,002
I found them, over by the wrecked plane.

442
00:39:24,002 --> 00:39:25,940
(gun firing)
- Somebody's coming.

443
00:39:25,940 --> 00:39:26,910
- They're French resistance

444
00:39:26,910 --> 00:39:28,770
who penetrated into German territory.

445
00:39:28,770 --> 00:39:31,087
Don't worry I'll help you across.

446
00:39:32,267 --> 00:39:35,017
(dramatic music)

447
00:39:50,266 --> 00:39:52,530
Tochiro take this with you.

448
00:39:52,530 --> 00:39:56,030
- Why that's--
- It's the one from the plane.

449
00:39:56,030 --> 00:39:56,997
Take it with you.

450
00:39:58,149 --> 00:40:00,280
- But this is your--

451
00:40:00,280 --> 00:40:01,410
- I would only give this to

452
00:40:01,410 --> 00:40:03,210
someone whom I could really trust.

453
00:40:03,210 --> 00:40:05,250
Someone who was truly a friend.

454
00:40:05,250 --> 00:40:07,443
Someone I could believe in.

455
00:40:07,443 --> 00:40:08,276
- Harlock.

456
00:40:13,500 --> 00:40:14,343
- [Phantom] Here.

457
00:40:15,338 --> 00:40:17,770
(gun firing)

458
00:40:17,770 --> 00:40:18,603
Farewell.

459
00:40:21,008 --> 00:40:23,223
- Harlock what are you going to do now?

460
00:40:24,710 --> 00:40:27,930
- I'm not the type who
would run off like a coward.

461
00:40:27,930 --> 00:40:29,570
A pirate must always be ready

462
00:40:29,570 --> 00:40:31,203
to answer for what he has done.

463
00:40:33,167 --> 00:40:35,570
Tochiro never give up your dream

464
00:40:35,570 --> 00:40:36,741
and make the most of your life.

465
00:40:36,741 --> 00:40:38,833
(gun firing)
(gasping)

466
00:40:38,833 --> 00:40:39,666
- Harlock.

467
00:40:40,991 --> 00:40:45,190
- I'm glad I could meet you
at the end of this stupid war.

468
00:40:45,190 --> 00:40:47,793
I wish we'd met in different times.

469
00:40:49,100 --> 00:40:50,390
- [Man] He's down in the river.

470
00:40:50,390 --> 00:40:51,820
Circle around to the right.

471
00:40:51,820 --> 00:40:52,653
- Harlock.

472
00:40:53,560 --> 00:40:54,783
Stay alive!

473
00:40:59,022 --> 00:41:02,540
Harlock, I'll remember you
for the rest of my life.

474
00:41:02,540 --> 00:41:05,100
My whole family will never forget you.

475
00:41:05,100 --> 00:41:06,900
Our friendship will never never die.

476
00:41:08,340 --> 00:41:09,173
Never die.

477
00:41:24,267 --> 00:41:27,100
(birds squawking)

478
00:41:34,300 --> 00:41:36,300
- [Tochiro] Over a thousand years ago

479
00:41:36,300 --> 00:41:38,053
our ancestors had been friends.

480
00:41:40,190 --> 00:41:43,223
- But I wonder why Zoll
gave the book back to me.

481
00:41:44,544 --> 00:41:47,200
- Harlock congratulations.

482
00:41:47,200 --> 00:41:49,400
My suspecting you of
being in the underground

483
00:41:49,400 --> 00:41:50,887
has all been cleared up.

484
00:41:50,887 --> 00:41:52,543
- [Zeda] And I am quite pleased.

485
00:41:53,720 --> 00:41:55,565
- According to Zoll's report

486
00:41:55,565 --> 00:41:58,450
the results of the analysis
proved you totally innocent

487
00:41:58,450 --> 00:41:59,850
along with your friend here.

488
00:42:01,690 --> 00:42:03,500
- I must ask your friend to leave us alone

489
00:42:03,500 --> 00:42:05,560
for I wish to talk to Harlock.

490
00:42:21,367 --> 00:42:22,200
- Harlock.

491
00:42:24,310 --> 00:42:28,470
We must have you pledge your
loyalty to Earth once again.

492
00:42:28,470 --> 00:42:31,330
- I have always fought for this planet

493
00:42:31,330 --> 00:42:34,360
in accordance with the laws
and rules of Earth at the time.

494
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:36,063
- Alright, good enough.

495
00:42:37,400 --> 00:42:39,540
We have decided to send a volunteer army

496
00:42:39,540 --> 00:42:41,240
to the planet Tokarga.
- Tokarga?

497
00:42:42,613 --> 00:42:44,470
- And I am assigning you the task

498
00:42:44,470 --> 00:42:45,910
of transporting the troops.

499
00:42:45,910 --> 00:42:47,710
- Why are you sending an army there?

500
00:42:50,350 --> 00:42:53,243
Why must Earthmen have to
go to Tokarga to fight?

501
00:42:56,310 --> 00:42:57,720
- Let me remind you that you have

502
00:42:57,720 --> 00:43:00,520
pledged your loyalty
to Earth and so have I.

503
00:43:00,520 --> 00:43:03,210
And now we are being
forced into a position

504
00:43:03,210 --> 00:43:05,310
where we must either
allow the mother to die

505
00:43:05,310 --> 00:43:06,820
or kill the stray dog.

506
00:43:06,820 --> 00:43:10,650
- So now Earth is the mother
and Tokarga is the stray dog.

507
00:43:10,650 --> 00:43:12,357
- For Illumidus the entire planet

508
00:43:12,357 --> 00:43:14,710
of Tokarga is of no further use.

509
00:43:14,710 --> 00:43:18,370
- You intend to annihilate
Torkarga, to liquidate it?

510
00:43:18,370 --> 00:43:20,350
And who in the universe can decide

511
00:43:20,350 --> 00:43:22,543
whether a planet is useless or not?

512
00:43:24,030 --> 00:43:26,060
Every single living thing in the universe

513
00:43:26,060 --> 00:43:28,740
has a right to life and now the mission

514
00:43:28,740 --> 00:43:30,560
to destroy Torkarga has to be carried out

515
00:43:30,560 --> 00:43:33,290
by Earthmen using my hands?

516
00:43:33,290 --> 00:43:34,960
The whole idea stinks.

517
00:43:34,960 --> 00:43:35,793
- Come back.

518
00:43:37,890 --> 00:43:39,860
We must cooperate with the Illumidus

519
00:43:39,860 --> 00:43:41,650
by sending a volunteer army.

520
00:43:41,650 --> 00:43:43,220
It's the only way they'll guarantee

521
00:43:43,220 --> 00:43:44,920
the safety of the Earth.

522
00:43:44,920 --> 00:43:47,000
You think the whole idea stinks,

523
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:49,330
then tell me if you
think it's a better idea

524
00:43:49,330 --> 00:43:51,963
to sacrifice the Earth for
another planet's safety?

525
00:43:54,657 --> 00:43:57,324
(ship rumbling)

526
00:44:21,663 --> 00:44:24,246
(wind howling)

527
00:44:37,642 --> 00:44:39,270
- [Tochiro] Hmm?

528
00:44:39,270 --> 00:44:43,620
- I am Emeraldas, a
freelance space trader,

529
00:44:43,620 --> 00:44:45,603
and I hold a legitimate license.

530
00:44:46,780 --> 00:44:49,800
I am no one's enemy and no one's ally.

531
00:44:49,800 --> 00:44:52,050
I'm a free space trader.

532
00:44:52,050 --> 00:44:52,903
Who are you?

533
00:44:53,810 --> 00:44:55,360
- [Tochiro] My name is Tochiro.

534
00:44:57,014 --> 00:44:59,987
- And what do you want?
- I'm looking for my friend.

535
00:45:00,970 --> 00:45:03,193
But your ship, she's
scorched pretty badly.

536
00:45:04,110 --> 00:45:05,380
- [Emeraldas] I made an error in crossing

537
00:45:05,380 --> 00:45:07,160
the Flame Stream Prominence.

538
00:45:07,160 --> 00:45:09,493
It's called the Owen
Stanley Witch of Space.

539
00:45:11,160 --> 00:45:13,730
Not only is there tremendous heat energy,

540
00:45:13,730 --> 00:45:16,913
but super gravitation that
pulls in any life reaction.

541
00:45:21,286 --> 00:45:23,869
(wind howling)

542
00:45:36,489 --> 00:45:38,745
(panting)

543
00:45:38,745 --> 00:45:40,665
- [La Mime] Zoll.

544
00:45:40,665 --> 00:45:41,498
(gasping)

545
00:45:41,498 --> 00:45:42,730
- What's wrong La Mime?

546
00:45:45,490 --> 00:45:47,003
It's dangerous to come here.

547
00:45:48,670 --> 00:45:51,700
- [La Mime] I know that, but--

548
00:45:51,700 --> 00:45:52,850
- Tell me what's wrong?

549
00:45:53,940 --> 00:45:55,890
- [La Mime] I heard the
top secret coded order

550
00:45:55,890 --> 00:45:58,445
sent to the general commander.

551
00:45:58,445 --> 00:45:59,362
- Ah?
- Hmm?

552
00:46:04,840 --> 00:46:06,140
- [La Mime] It's Torkarga.

553
00:46:09,140 --> 00:46:09,973
- What about it?

554
00:46:12,530 --> 00:46:13,980
- [La Mime] They're going to...

555
00:46:15,980 --> 00:46:17,380
- [Maya On Radio] No matter how great

556
00:46:17,380 --> 00:46:21,940
the bitter agony may be
consider it as the sigh

557
00:46:21,940 --> 00:46:25,050
of the beautiful future yet to come.

558
00:46:25,050 --> 00:46:28,510
Do not let despair lure you to defeat.

559
00:46:28,510 --> 00:46:32,943
The crisp air at dawn, the
fresh wind, remember it all.

560
00:46:33,990 --> 00:46:37,110
Remember the time we ran hand and hand

561
00:46:37,110 --> 00:46:42,110
over the green, green fields,
remember with love, remember.

562
00:46:43,891 --> 00:46:46,641
(dramatic music)

563
00:46:55,787 --> 00:46:57,318
(panting)

564
00:46:57,318 --> 00:46:58,659
(suspenseful music)

565
00:46:58,659 --> 00:47:00,231
(guns firing)
(yelling)

566
00:47:00,231 --> 00:47:02,258
(thumping)
(groaning)

567
00:47:02,258 --> 00:47:03,856
(gun firing)

568
00:47:03,856 --> 00:47:05,296
(yelling)

569
00:47:05,296 --> 00:47:07,796
(guns firing)

570
00:47:16,399 --> 00:47:18,825
(yelling)

571
00:47:18,825 --> 00:47:21,325
(guns firing)

572
00:47:32,780 --> 00:47:33,613
- Harlock.

573
00:47:35,929 --> 00:47:38,346
- Maya, look out, take cover.

574
00:47:40,023 --> 00:47:40,856
Maya.

575
00:47:44,108 --> 00:47:45,539
Maya!

576
00:47:45,539 --> 00:47:48,039
(guns firing)

577
00:47:49,083 --> 00:47:51,250
(yelling)

578
00:47:52,207 --> 00:47:54,707
(guns firing)

579
00:47:56,618 --> 00:47:57,451
- Harlock!

580
00:47:58,638 --> 00:47:59,471
- Maya.

581
00:48:02,716 --> 00:48:03,549
Maya.

582
00:48:06,017 --> 00:48:09,565
(gun firing)
(dramatic music)

583
00:48:09,565 --> 00:48:10,398
Maya.

584
00:48:17,870 --> 00:48:22,537
(gun firing)
(groaning)

585
00:49:02,256 --> 00:49:03,089
- Harlock.

586
00:49:04,409 --> 00:49:05,680
No.

587
00:49:05,680 --> 00:49:07,073
Don't come closer.

588
00:49:07,970 --> 00:49:10,041
Your coming this far,

589
00:49:10,041 --> 00:49:12,553
it's more than enough to make me happy.

590
00:49:13,882 --> 00:49:15,465
Hurry and get away.

591
00:49:18,993 --> 00:49:22,113
- How can I leave without you?

592
00:49:23,280 --> 00:49:24,113
- Oh no.

593
00:49:24,963 --> 00:49:27,590
Don't come any closer.

594
00:49:27,590 --> 00:49:29,489
Don't, don't throw your life away.

595
00:49:29,489 --> 00:49:31,323
(groaning)

596
00:49:31,323 --> 00:49:35,483
Stay alive and someday I
know we'll be together again.

597
00:49:40,260 --> 00:49:42,093
Harlock, please don't.

598
00:49:44,505 --> 00:49:46,636
Don't come any closer.

599
00:49:46,636 --> 00:49:47,469
Harlock.

600
00:49:48,409 --> 00:49:51,159
(dramatic music)

601
00:50:01,228 --> 00:50:04,457
Please don't. (crying)

602
00:50:04,457 --> 00:50:05,750
- [Man] Fire!

603
00:50:05,750 --> 00:50:07,167
- [Phantom] Maya!

604
00:50:26,792 --> 00:50:29,875
(strained breathing)

605
00:50:31,120 --> 00:50:32,723
- Harlock, what's wrong?

606
00:50:33,560 --> 00:50:35,480
- A little man called Tochiro,

607
00:50:35,480 --> 00:50:36,980
have you seen him around here?

608
00:50:38,130 --> 00:50:40,640
- [Tochiro] Hey, you finally came.

609
00:50:40,640 --> 00:50:42,660
- [Emeraldas] And just
where have you been hiding?

610
00:50:42,660 --> 00:50:44,660
- [Tochiro] I've been repairing the ship.

611
00:50:44,660 --> 00:50:47,190
I still need one part to make it perfect,

612
00:50:47,190 --> 00:50:49,640
but even without it she's ready to fly.

613
00:50:49,640 --> 00:50:52,450
- [Phantom] You mean you
fixed it, it's ready to go?

614
00:50:52,450 --> 00:50:53,850
- [Tochiro] Don't you believe me?

615
00:50:53,850 --> 00:50:57,573
- It's not that, can she fly?
- She sure can.

616
00:51:00,350 --> 00:51:03,110
Hey why don't you come aboard and see?

617
00:51:03,110 --> 00:51:04,297
(groaning)

618
00:51:04,297 --> 00:51:05,550
- Harlock.
- Harlock.

619
00:51:05,550 --> 00:51:09,503
Harlock, what's wrong?
(unsettling music)

620
00:51:14,553 --> 00:51:18,660
- [Maya On Radio] This is
the voice of Free Arcadia.

621
00:51:18,660 --> 00:51:23,310
If you let it burn only ashes will remain,

622
00:51:23,310 --> 00:51:27,740
but a true living fire of
hope will never die out.

623
00:51:27,740 --> 00:51:31,430
Some day like a forest fire it will spread

624
00:51:31,430 --> 00:51:35,130
from one to the other increasing its power

625
00:51:35,130 --> 00:51:39,103
and that hope will create
a new and beautiful future.

626
00:51:40,090 --> 00:51:43,430
Even if you set off
tomorrow to a distant place

627
00:51:43,430 --> 00:51:45,660
no one will think badly of you

628
00:51:45,660 --> 00:51:50,199
for people do have faith in
you that you will return.

629
00:51:50,199 --> 00:51:52,116
(glass cracking)

630
00:51:52,116 --> 00:51:54,283
(gasping)

631
00:51:59,758 --> 00:52:02,758
(suspenseful music)

632
00:52:06,890 --> 00:52:08,490
- [Tochiro] She's been captured.

633
00:52:10,370 --> 00:52:12,293
- I can almost picture that poor girl.

634
00:52:13,150 --> 00:52:15,090
In her heart she's not
only holding the torch

635
00:52:15,090 --> 00:52:16,860
for her oppressed people,

636
00:52:16,860 --> 00:52:19,730
but she seems to be in love
with a particular person.

637
00:52:19,730 --> 00:52:21,380
That broadcast we just heard

638
00:52:21,380 --> 00:52:23,063
must've been a personal message.

639
00:52:25,230 --> 00:52:28,223
She put her life in danger to
send that message to someone.

640
00:52:30,576 --> 00:52:31,576
- Emeraldas.

641
00:52:33,850 --> 00:52:37,520
Would you do me a favor
and let me steal your ship?

642
00:52:37,520 --> 00:52:38,870
- [Tochiro] What did you say?

643
00:52:38,870 --> 00:52:42,260
- Because I must escape from Earth.

644
00:52:42,260 --> 00:52:43,910
- [Zoll] I can't let you do that.

645
00:52:53,500 --> 00:52:56,310
- You're just as rotten
as the rest of them.

646
00:52:56,310 --> 00:52:58,850
You've turned yourself
into a Illumidus dog.

647
00:52:58,850 --> 00:53:01,153
- [La Mime] Harlock, wait a moment.

648
00:53:01,153 --> 00:53:03,233
Zoll didn't come here to arrest you.

649
00:53:04,810 --> 00:53:07,343
We've come to take over Emeraldas' ship.

650
00:53:08,720 --> 00:53:11,080
Our people want to go back to Torkarga.

651
00:53:11,080 --> 00:53:12,290
- That's enough La Mime.

652
00:53:12,290 --> 00:53:13,760
They've got nothing to do with this.

653
00:53:13,760 --> 00:53:14,603
- Oh?

654
00:53:18,910 --> 00:53:23,323
- [La Mime] My planet was
totally destroyed by Illumidus

655
00:53:24,740 --> 00:53:26,563
and reverted to a primitive state.

656
00:53:27,910 --> 00:53:30,133
The sight I saw from the refugee ship.

657
00:53:31,100 --> 00:53:33,070
I can never forget the grief I felt

658
00:53:33,070 --> 00:53:35,840
when our planet lost its glow.

659
00:53:35,840 --> 00:53:38,010
And now Zoll and all the
other Torkarga people

660
00:53:38,010 --> 00:53:39,793
are facing the same tragedy.

661
00:53:40,920 --> 00:53:44,513
If Zoll and the others escape
Illumidus will retaliate.

662
00:53:45,800 --> 00:53:49,333
Still they're driven by their
love for their mother planet.

663
00:53:50,270 --> 00:53:53,760
If destruction is inevitable they want

664
00:53:53,760 --> 00:53:56,423
to perish on Torkarga with their families.

665
00:53:57,560 --> 00:54:00,280
They need a ship to return to Torkarga

666
00:54:01,590 --> 00:54:03,003
and that's why we've come.

667
00:54:04,237 --> 00:54:06,987
(dramatic music)

668
00:54:08,520 --> 00:54:10,770
The same thing will
happen to Earth some day.

669
00:54:11,860 --> 00:54:15,193
For now I beg of you, let
Zoll and the others go.

670
00:54:16,840 --> 00:54:18,390
- I'm sorry for what I've said.

671
00:54:20,400 --> 00:54:21,233
I understand.

672
00:54:30,980 --> 00:54:33,390
- [Murigson] All our forces
have taken emergency positions.

673
00:54:33,390 --> 00:54:37,290
- Hmm, I have been overlooking
those underground broadcasts

674
00:54:37,290 --> 00:54:41,060
so far thinking it would give
the Earthmen a will to work.

675
00:54:41,060 --> 00:54:43,870
- Yes, but I thought today's broadcast

676
00:54:43,870 --> 00:54:45,270
sounded like a message to start

677
00:54:45,270 --> 00:54:46,920
a full scale revolt here on Earth

678
00:54:47,770 --> 00:54:49,940
or possibly urging them to escape.

679
00:54:49,940 --> 00:54:52,150
- Don't worry they can't go anywhere.

680
00:54:52,150 --> 00:54:53,760
They're like rats in a cage making

681
00:54:53,760 --> 00:54:56,033
a lot of noise, but they can't escape.

682
00:54:57,685 --> 00:54:59,390
- If Tochiro hadn't repaired my ship

683
00:54:59,390 --> 00:55:03,010
it would've been abandoned,
therefor take it.

684
00:55:03,010 --> 00:55:06,120
- [Tochiro] Wait, if you use this ship

685
00:55:06,120 --> 00:55:07,970
no matter what she says
Emeraldas will lose

686
00:55:07,970 --> 00:55:09,623
her free space traders license.

687
00:55:11,000 --> 00:55:13,890
Also as soon as Zoll takes off

688
00:55:13,890 --> 00:55:17,060
they will immediately
commence to attack Torkarga.

689
00:55:17,060 --> 00:55:18,360
So we'll use another ship.

690
00:55:20,299 --> 00:55:22,850
Harlock, let us go to Torkarga

691
00:55:22,850 --> 00:55:24,450
in place of Zoll and the others.

692
00:55:26,450 --> 00:55:31,033
I've been waiting a long
time, such a long time.

693
00:55:34,230 --> 00:55:37,160
Struggling to stay alive,
living like a beggar.

694
00:55:37,160 --> 00:55:38,933
I've been waiting for this chance.

695
00:55:44,590 --> 00:55:46,780
Waiting for the day when I

696
00:55:46,780 --> 00:55:49,673
could set out in my own spaceship.

697
00:55:51,260 --> 00:55:53,640
- In your own spaceship?

698
00:55:53,640 --> 00:55:55,050
- [Tochiro] I've been
looking for a captain

699
00:55:55,050 --> 00:55:57,550
worthy enough to entrust
him with my spaceship.

700
00:55:57,550 --> 00:56:00,123
- This spaceship, where is it?

701
00:56:01,474 --> 00:56:03,690
(laughing)

702
00:56:03,690 --> 00:56:07,023
- I got one, I've got one. (laughing)

703
00:56:08,250 --> 00:56:12,423
- Your, you really are incredible.

704
00:56:16,716 --> 00:56:18,090
- Zoll, what do you say?

705
00:56:18,090 --> 00:56:22,060
With their spaceship and with
their help perhaps we could--

706
00:56:22,060 --> 00:56:24,820
- No this is strictly a Torkarga problem.

707
00:56:24,820 --> 00:56:27,140
Just let us have the use of the ship.

708
00:56:27,140 --> 00:56:29,163
- [Tochiro] No I can't let you do that.

709
00:56:31,570 --> 00:56:35,650
The ship is me, every bit of it is me

710
00:56:35,650 --> 00:56:37,100
and it won't move without me.

711
00:56:39,170 --> 00:56:41,263
- [La Mime] Zoll let me go in your place.

712
00:56:42,770 --> 00:56:46,623
Please, and ask Harlock and
Tochiro to go to Torkarga.

713
00:56:49,020 --> 00:56:52,340
In return you stay here
and pretend loyalty

714
00:56:52,340 --> 00:56:55,113
to Illumidus and protect the Earthmen.

715
00:56:55,986 --> 00:56:58,560
Illumidus is much too strong as an enemy.

716
00:56:58,560 --> 00:57:01,440
The only way to ruin them is
to take invisible measures

717
00:57:01,440 --> 00:57:04,700
like bacteria spoiling it from inside.

718
00:57:04,700 --> 00:57:07,425
- You want me to be the
bacteria here on Earth?

719
00:57:07,425 --> 00:57:08,423
- [La Mime] Yes.

720
00:57:09,580 --> 00:57:12,023
- And we'll be the bacteria on Torkarga.

721
00:57:14,781 --> 00:57:16,460
- Zoll I will go with them on the ship

722
00:57:16,460 --> 00:57:19,173
as a delegate of Torkarga
and you take over here.

723
00:57:23,870 --> 00:57:27,370
- I've been a dog, a dog begging
for the lives of my people,

724
00:57:27,370 --> 00:57:31,620
a dog that fights as
instrument of Illumidus.

725
00:57:31,620 --> 00:57:33,743
The people who remained on Torkarga

726
00:57:33,743 --> 00:57:36,193
have been dreaming of
a day of deliverance.

727
00:57:37,480 --> 00:57:39,960
Believing that we will come
back to rescue them some day

728
00:57:39,960 --> 00:57:42,833
as they hold their breath
under Illumidus's oppression.

729
00:57:44,260 --> 00:57:46,780
When I close my eyes I
can see my little brother

730
00:57:46,780 --> 00:57:49,430
and sister praying and
waiting for my return

731
00:57:50,630 --> 00:57:52,410
bearing so much bitterness and yet

732
00:57:52,410 --> 00:57:54,563
praying for me to come back and save them.

733
00:57:55,785 --> 00:57:58,535
(dramatic music)

734
00:58:05,630 --> 00:58:07,992
Tochiro hurry to Torkarga.

735
00:58:07,992 --> 00:58:10,075
(crying)

736
00:58:13,960 --> 00:58:17,080
I am grateful to you for
making all this possible.

737
00:58:17,080 --> 00:58:17,913
Thank you.

738
00:58:24,738 --> 00:58:29,571
(crying)
(dramatic music)

739
00:58:32,260 --> 00:58:34,140
- Now for the future of Torkarga

740
00:58:38,140 --> 00:58:40,155
and to the men of true courage,

741
00:58:40,155 --> 00:58:44,843
Zoll of Torkaraga, for
Harlock, Tochiro and La Mime

742
00:58:44,843 --> 00:58:47,570
and all the rest of you brave men.

743
00:58:47,570 --> 00:58:49,780
(speaking in a foreign language)

744
00:58:49,780 --> 00:58:51,080
- [La Mime] It's a Torkargan word

745
00:58:51,080 --> 00:58:52,943
to toast with true friends.

746
00:58:54,510 --> 00:58:58,213
It means we pledge true
friendship with our blood.

747
00:58:59,780 --> 00:59:03,863
(speaking in a foreign language)

748
00:59:16,944 --> 00:59:19,444
(guns firing)

749
00:59:30,974 --> 00:59:35,641
(yelling)
(guns firing)

750
00:59:48,451 --> 00:59:51,034
(wind howling)

751
01:00:15,047 --> 01:00:19,967
- Take this to Harlock, please hurry.

752
01:00:19,967 --> 01:00:22,217
(coughing)

753
01:00:23,082 --> 01:00:26,082
(suspenseful music)

754
01:00:43,662 --> 01:00:48,329
(guns firing)
(yelling)

755
01:01:10,550 --> 01:01:13,273
- Interesting, let's see
just how far they can go.

756
01:01:24,900 --> 01:01:26,330
- [Man] Maya sent this.

757
01:01:26,330 --> 01:01:29,823
She made it especially for
you and asked that you use it.

758
01:01:32,113 --> 01:01:34,063
- [Tochiro] Harlock we've got to hurry.

759
01:01:35,660 --> 01:01:37,843
- Don't worry, we'll protect Maya.

760
01:01:39,970 --> 01:01:42,860
Farewell and I wish you a successful trip.

761
01:01:50,139 --> 01:01:50,972
- Harlock.

762
01:01:52,159 --> 01:01:55,159
(suspenseful music)

763
01:02:37,270 --> 01:02:38,103
Down here.

764
01:02:39,252 --> 01:02:42,252
(suspenseful music)

765
01:02:51,870 --> 01:02:53,503
- Maya, you shouldn't be up.

766
01:02:54,909 --> 01:02:57,050
- I haven't got too much longer to live

767
01:02:58,050 --> 01:03:02,393
so please let me see Harlock take off.

768
01:03:04,100 --> 01:03:06,870
- [Tochiro] And this, the
ship I built to fulfill

769
01:03:06,870 --> 01:03:10,373
our ancestor's dream
and I named her Arcadia.

770
01:03:11,210 --> 01:03:12,710
- Arcadia?

771
01:03:12,710 --> 01:03:14,660
- Only the name Arcadia would be suitable

772
01:03:14,660 --> 01:03:16,163
for a ship that we launch.

773
01:03:17,300 --> 01:03:18,133
- Arcadia.

774
01:03:19,842 --> 01:03:23,400
- And this is our ship.
- Arcadia.

775
01:03:23,400 --> 01:03:24,383
Our own ship.

776
01:03:33,231 --> 01:03:36,064
And you built this?
- That's right.

777
01:03:37,090 --> 01:03:38,850
A ship I built with the technology

778
01:03:38,850 --> 01:03:41,000
I inherited from my ancestors.

779
01:03:41,000 --> 01:03:43,977
It took a long time, but Harlock

780
01:03:44,820 --> 01:03:48,183
this is the ship to achieve our dream.

781
01:03:49,139 --> 01:03:51,889
(dramatic music)

782
01:04:12,460 --> 01:04:13,293
What's that?

783
01:04:34,280 --> 01:04:35,703
It's fantastic.

784
01:04:36,550 --> 01:04:39,090
Do you want to go and see Maya?

785
01:04:39,090 --> 01:04:41,240
- She wouldn't want me to do that.

786
01:04:41,240 --> 01:04:42,780
She'd be upset.

787
01:04:42,780 --> 01:04:43,613
